            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-03T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="811" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114 Pacific War/3–347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Supreme Commander for the Allied Powers in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacArthur</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-03T19:00:00-05:00">March 3, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>74. For Political Adviser. In light of Nanking’s 340 (repeated Tokyo Feb 22) Dept
                    feels inadvisable U. S. initiate action at this time toward repatriation Jap
                    holdout forces Manchuria.</p>
                <p>Sent Tokyo repeated Nanking. Embassy pass copy to Underwood.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
